# =============================================================================
# REAL MEDIA FILES (NEVER COMMIT)
# =============================================================================
# Block ALL production media formats to prevent accidental large file commits.
# Only synthetic test fixtures (generated at runtime) are allowed in the repo.
#
# WHY: Real media files are:
#   - Too large for Git (multi-GB files destroy clone/fetch performance)
#   - Contain proprietary content (legal/licensing risk)
#   - Unnecessary (tests use synthetic fixtures)
#
# ENFORCEMENT:
#   - This .gitignore blocks common media extensions
#   - Pre-commit hook validates file sizes
#   - QA documentation defines fixture policy
#
# If you need test media:
#   - Use synthetic fixtures in qa/fixtures/ (generated at runtime, also ignored)
#   - Reference external media via symlinks or environment variables
#   - Document external media requirements in test docstrings

# Video container formats (uncompressed/mezzanine)
*.mxf
*.ari
*.arri
*.r3d
*.braw
*.dng
*.dpx
*.exr

# Video container formats (delivery/edit)
# Note: *.ts is MPEG Transport Stream, but conflicts with TypeScript files
# So we specifically exclude media directories instead of blanket *.ts
*.mov
*.mp4
*.avi
*.mkv
*.webm
*.m4v
*.mpg
*.mpeg
*.m2ts
*.mts
# Transport streams - use more specific patterns to avoid TypeScript conflicts
**/test_media/**/*.ts
**/forge-tests/**/*.ts
**/samples/**/*.ts
**/output/**/*.ts

